–> > The purpose of this document is to simulataneously analyze a dataset containing wages of 80 workers a a single manufacturing firm. We have been assigned whether or not age has a quadratic effect on predicted wages. The dataset contains data on the hourly wage, age and education of the employees. The second dataset we will analyze is the Ann Arbor dataset. This dataset conttains data on a portion of the rental market in Ann Arbor, MI. The data includes the monthly rent, number of bedrooms, and the square footage of 40 rental properties.

1c:Estimating another multple regression model of Wage using Age/Education

2a: Ann Arbor data: Plot rent against each of the 3 predictor variables

AnnArbor <-read_csv(file = "AnnArbor.csv")
library(ggplot2)
library(readxl)

plot_relationship <- function(df, x_var) {
  ggplot(df, aes_string(x = x_var, y = "Rent")) +
    geom_point(alpha = 0.6) +
    geom_smooth(method = "lm", color = "blue", se = FALSE) + 
    geom_smooth(method = "loess", color = "red", se = FALSE) + 
    labs(title = paste("Rent vs", x_var), x = x_var, y = "Rent") +
    theme_minimal()
}

plot1 <- plot_relationship(AnnArbor, "Beds")
plot2 <- plot_relationship(AnnArbor, "Baths")
plot3 <- plot_relationship(AnnArbor, "Sqft")


library(gridExtra)
grid.arrange(plot1, plot2, plot3, ncol = 2)

–> The code above plotted Rent against each of the three predictor variables: Beds, Baths, and Sqft. The purpose was to evaulate whether the relationship is best captured by a line or a curve. Based on the visualization, we can see that the relationship between Rent and Beds is best captured by a line, indicating a linear relationship. Secondly, the relationship between rent and baths is best captured by a line as well, this relationship is fairly linear. Though there seems to be a slight curve in the higher numbers. The relationship between Rent and Sqft is best captured by a curve. The variables that may benefit from a log-transformation would be Sqft. We can conclude this based on the visualization showing that the curve is especially present at lower sqft values.
